            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">34. Collapse<br />\nA 60-year-old diabetic man recovering from sepsis after collapsing at home was<br />\ntreated with appropriate antibiotics after blood culture and aggressive fluid<br />\nmanagement with 0.9 per cent saline for 2 days for hypotension. Although blood<br />\npressure returned to normal, the patient had the following abnormal biochemical<br />\nblood results:<br />\npH 7.32<br />\nPCO2 5.2<br />\nPO2 11.1<br />\nSodium 147 mmol/L<br />\nPotassium 3.5 mmol/L<br />\nChloride 119 mmol/L<br />\nBicarbonate 19.5<br />\nThe most likely diagnosis is:</p>"
